<div id="sharetools-story" class="sharetools theme-classic sharetools-story" data-shares="email|Email,facebook|Share,twitter|Tweet,save|Save,show-all|More,ad" data-url="//learning.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/03/04/unexpected-africa-investigating-new-ways-to-think-about-the-continent/" data-title="Unexpected Africa: Investigating New Ways to Think About the Continent" data-description="In this lesson, we seek to challenge preconceptions with articles that offer new perspectives and defy stereotypes. From poverty and war to arts and entertainment, the worldâs second largest continent is far more complex than it may seem.">
