		<div class="comment-content" style="display:block;">

			<p>Another wonderful lesson plan that helps rid students of preconceived notions and generalizations about places outside of the United States. It has never been more important in education to teach students that the world is a complex, ever-changing place, especially in this era of globalization. I love the attention to how technology affects culture, literature, and world economies. This lesson is a great source for interdisciplinary unit plans and synthesis. Thank you.</p>
<p>James Mulhern, <a href="//www.synthesizingeducation.net" rel="nofollow">//www.synthesizingeducation.net</a></p>

